import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['precipitation'] = pd.to_numeric(data['precipitation'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['precipitation'])
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['precipitation'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Precipitation (inches)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['temp_max'])
    plt.title('How does the maximum temperature vary over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Maximum Temperature (F)')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    weather_counts = data['weather'].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = weather_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('Weather Condition')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common weather condition observed in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    for i, v in enumerate(weather_counts):
        ax.text(i, v + 10, str(v), ha='center')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

    return plt
